summary:
The Bhutan film trust supports independent Bhutanese film makers in bringing their productions to the international film market. The trust supports research, production,  postproduction and PR and assist with legal advice, marketing and international networks. The Trust is a bhutan+partners initiative 
Bhutan+partners is an expert and resource centre; matching people and companies from Bhutan to Europe and vice versa with a focus on culture, sports and business. 
Since 2002 bhutan+partners have succesfully connected people and organisations involved in business development (green and clean economy), film/book production, sports and cultural events. Bhutan+partners is responsible for organizing remarkable events: 
The Other Final (2002), BLøF to Bhutan (2006), Piano to Bhutan (2008), Himalaya Trial (2008), Sports coalition in Action (2009-2012), Queen of Bhutan tulip ( 2012) and the 2012 film production: ...86 centimetres. www.86centimetres.org. Bhutan+partners co-ordinates the Bhutan Film Trust, since 2014. 

De bhutan film trust ondersteunt onafhankelijke getalenteerde bhutanese filmmakers die hun films internationaal willen presenteren. De Trust een een bhutan+partners initiatief en wordt eind 2016 overgedragen aan Bhutan.
Bhutan+partners is een kennis en expert center; bhutan+partners verbindt mensen en organisaties in Europa met Bhutan sinds 2002 met focus op cultuur, sport en ondernemen. Met een groot netwerk onder overheid, intellectuelen, journalisten, artiesten en zakenmensen, weet bhutan+partners creatieve en inspirerende verbindingen te maken.
Bhutan+partners waren onder andere betrokken bij: The Other Final (2002), Bløf to Bhutan (2006), Piano to Bhutan (2008), Himalya Trial (2008), Sport Coalition in Action (2009-2012), Queen of Bhutan Tulip ( 2012), 86 centimetres... (2012) oprichting en coordinatie van Bhutan Film Trust 2014 


Specialismen
matchmaking, film industry, culture, philosophy, B2B
